/** @format */ import React from 'react'; import profile from '../images/profile.png'; import './CV.css'; const CV = () => { return (

Executive Chef Yannick

French native, Yannick received his formal culinary training in Michelin star restaurant at the age of 16; apprentice in Pastry, Yannick has develop a profound culinary knowledge in the kitchen and pastry division, before his first chef de cuisine position at the age of 27.

Chef Yannick brings over 30 years experience, with exposure working in Europe, Asia and Middle East. That allows chef Yannick to develop extensive knowledge in Asian and International cuisine, yet Classical, Modern and with a Gourmet flair.

Currently based “in house chef” since 2008 at Morgan Stanley Hong Kong, chef Yannick works as Executive Chef managing his team in a corporate environment, various nature of events, business, summit, conference and for both internal and external events covering the whole APAC region.

Working Approach

  • Client first, understand the objectives, core values and vision of the company.
  • Adhere & follow the principle of think, do, measure, correct & improve continuously.
  • Result-oriented, adopt actions to circumstances to obtain the best possible result.
  • Create a dynamic structure in the kitchen, products, quality process & resources.
  • Hands-on, coach & lead a team with detail minded / team building / training and budget targets.
); }; export default CV;
